## Pattern 2: Route Handler

`src/app/api/**/route.ts` — the only HTTP entry point for the browser, external
services, and the Vercel runtime (cron / queues / webhooks).

### Use when

#### Client-callable JSON APIs

```typescript
// src/app/api/gen-tasks/route.ts
import { NextRequest } from 'next/server';
import { requireAuth } from '@/server/api/auth';
import { ok, fail, ErrorCode } from '@/server/api/response';
import { listGenTasksForHistory } from '@/server/loaders/gen-task-history';

export async function GET(req: NextRequest) {
  const auth = await requireAuth(req);
  if (!auth.ok) return auth.response;
  try {
    const tasks = await listGenTasksForHistory({ uid: auth.user.uid, limit: 20, offset: 0 });
    return ok({ tasks });
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[gen-tasks] Error:', error);
    return fail(ErrorCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
  }
}
```

#### AI / streaming responses

Use the AI SDK and Vercel AI Gateway. Prefer `"provider/model"` strings through
the Gateway over direct provider packages.

```typescript
// src/app/api/chat/route.ts
import { streamText } from 'ai';

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages } = await req.json();
  const result = streamText({ model: 'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4', messages });
  return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse();
}
```

#### Webhooks (`/api/webhooks/*`)

Verify the signature, log, then dispatch to a Server Handler. Always return a
200 once the event is durably accepted (idempotency keys live in the DB).

#### Cron (`/api/cron/*`)

Listed in `vercel.json` (or `vercel.ts`). Verify the cron header / secret, then
delegate to a Server Handler.

#### Queues (`/api/queues/*`)

Vercel Queues delivery target. Verify, dedupe by idempotency key, run a Server
Handler.

#### Realtime SSE (`/api/realtime/*`)

Publish via Redis, subscribe per-connection. Auth at the route boundary.

### Don't use when

- It's just a server-rendered read (use a Server Loader instead — saves a hop).
- The work is long-running and can outlive the HTTP timeout (push to a queue).

